[[马拉地人|马拉地人]]主要居于[[马哈拉施特拉邦|马哈拉施特拉邦]]，多信仰印度教。马拉地人名一般包含三节，依次是个人名，父名或夫名，姓氏（已婚女子从夫姓）。例如：

* 马哈德夫·戈文德·拉纳德（Mahadev Govind Ranade）：马哈德夫是个人名，戈文德是父名，拉纳德是姓氏。
* 乔茨娜·穆孔德·坎德卡尔（Jyotsna Mukund Khandekar）：乔茨娜是个人名，穆孔德是夫名，坎德卡尔是夫姓<ref>{{cite book|last1=Sharma|first1=D.D.|title=Panorama of Indian anthroponomy : (an historical, socio-cultural & linguistic analysis of Indian personal names|date=2005|publisher=Mittal Publications|location=New Delhi, India|isbn=9788183240789|page=192|url=https://books.google.com/?id=a4rccspy46sC&pg=PR5&dq=%22hindu+personal+names%22+#v=onepage&q=%22hindu%20personal%20names%22%20maharashtra&f=false}}</ref>。

马拉地印度教徒的个人名来源多样，可以是[[罗摩衍那|罗摩衍那]]和[[摩诃婆罗多|摩诃婆罗多]]史诗中的人物；可以是圣河名，如[[亚穆纳河|亚穆纳河]]（Yamuna）、[[哥达瓦里河|哥达瓦里河]]（Godavari）；历史明君，如[[希瓦吉|希瓦吉]]（Shivaji）、[[阿育王|阿育王]]（Ashoka）；马拉地圣人，如{{le|图卡拉姆|Tukaram}}、{{le|德尼亚内什瓦尔|Dnyaneshwar}}、{{le|贾娜巴伊|Janabai}}；现代文学人物，体育人物或名演员的名字；女子会以花卉、珠宝、天体名取名<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Dhongde |first1=R. V. |title=Personal Names in Marathi |journal=Bulletin of the Deccan College Post-Graduate and Research Institute |date=1986 |volume=45 |pages=25–36 |jstor=42930151 }}</ref>。

许多马拉地姓氏源于地名，后缀以-kar（卡尔），意为“来自某地”{{sfn|Chopra|1982|p=52}}。如久纳尔卡尔（Junnarkar）源于[[久纳尔|久纳尔]]。还有源于家族职业和商业贸易品的姓氏，如昆巴尔（Kumbhar）、苏塔尔（Sutar）、帕蒂尔（Patil）、德赛（Desai）、乔希（Joshi）等<ref>{{cite book|last1=Kulkarni|first1=A.R|title=Maharashtra in the Age of Shivaji|date=1969|publisher=R.J. Deshmukh Deshmukh|page=32|url=https://books.google.com/?id=zJNirJVU9PUC&q=patilki+brahmin&dq=patilki+brahmin|accessdate=2018-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Chatterjee|first1=Ramananda|title=The Modern Review, Volume 16|publisher=Modern Review Office|page=604|url=https://books.google.com/?id=1l_k7kNP95QC&q=patilki+brahmin&dq=patilki+brahmin|accessdate=2018-04-02|year=1914}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Gaborieau|first1=Marc|last2=Thorner|first2=Alice|title=Colloques internationaux du Centre national de la recherche scientifique, Issue 582|date=1979|publisher=Ed. du Centre national de la recherche scientifique, 1979|pages=201, 202|quote=Patilki vatan is both coveted and fought over: Brahmins, Marathas and Mahars may all be past and present sharers in}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Proceedings of the Session, Volume 38|publisher=Superintendent Government Printing, India, 1967|date=1967|quote=Most of the Brahmin families hereditarily enjoyed the patilki (village headmanship) or kulkarnigiri (village accountancy) of villages}}</ref><ref name="IWI">{{cite journal |title=The Illustrated Weekly of India |volume=91 |issue=3|date=July 1970 |publisher=Bennett, Coleman & Company |page=12 |quote=Generally speaking, excepting names such as Kulkarni, Thackerey, Chitnis, Deshmukh, Deshpande, which are common to many communities in Maharashtra, a C.K.P. can be recognised by his surname. }}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Home, Family and Kinship in Maharashtra|editor1=Irina Glushkova |editor2= Rajendra Vora |publisher=Oxford University Press|page=118|quote= The wada tells us of a story of three generations of a family called Deshpande who belong to the Deshastha Brahmin caste. ....Spread all over Maharashtra as a result of this process, Deshastha Brahmans held, in particular, the office of kulkarni.}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Hassan|first1=Syed Siraj ul|title=The Castes and Tribes of H.E.H. the Nizam's Dominions, Volume 1|publisher=Times Press|url=https://books.google.com/?id=lYSd-3yL9h0C&pg=PA111&dq=desai+deshastha+brahmin#v=onepage&q=desai%20deshastha%20brahmin&f=false|accessdate=2018-04-02|isbn=9788120604889|year=1989}}</ref>。

历史上著名的马拉地领袖的姓氏都是他们的氏族名，如贾达夫（Jadhav）、博萨莱（Bhosale）、恰范（Chavan）、欣德（Shinde）、帕瓦尔（Pawar）等<ref name="Dumont1980">{{cite book|author=Louis Dumont|title=Homo hierarchicus: the caste system and its implications|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XsOtRGdvIigC&pg=PA121|accessdate=2011-05-13|year=1980|publisher=University of Chicago Press|isbn=978-0-226-16963-7|pages=121|archive-date=2020-08-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200805152120/https://books.google.com/books?id=XsOtRGdvIigC&pg=PA121|dead-url=no}}</ref>。马拉地最大的种姓{{le|昆比|Kunbi}}，其成员的姓氏也有许多氏族名，皆为其宗主领袖所属氏族；亦有可能表达其正试图晋升阶层<ref name="O'Hanlon2002">{{cite book|author=Rosalind O'Hanlon|title=Caste, Conflict and Ideology: Mahatma Jotirao Phule and Low Caste Protest in Nineteenth-Century Western India|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5kMrsTj1NeYC&pg=PA17|accessdate=2011-05-13|date=2002-08-22|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-0-521-52308-0|pages=17|archive-date=2020-08-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200805193558/https://books.google.com/books?id=5kMrsTj1NeYC&pg=PA17|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

=== 克什米尔人名 ===
[[克什米尔人|克什米尔人]]的人名有两到三节，依次是名、中间名（可有可无）、姓。如[[贾瓦哈拉尔·尼赫鲁|贾瓦哈·拉尔·尼赫鲁]]（Jawahar Lal Nehru）。

昵称经常取代姓氏出现，所以一些不同的姓氏可能出自同一家族，如尼赫鲁（Nehru）和拉兹丹（Razdan）可能都归属于考尔（Kaul）家族<ref>{{cite book |author1=Jawaharlal Nehru |title=Toward Freedom: An Autobiography of Jawaharlal Nehru |isbn=9781299411050 |pages=16 |publisher=John Day Co. |year=1942 |url=https://www.questia.com/PM.qst?a=o&d=74007923 |access-date=2020-07-02 |archive-date=2008-03-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080321204959/http://www.questia.com/PM.qst?a=o&d=74007923 |dead-url=no }} Nehru Says: ''We were Kashmiris. Over two hundred years ago, early in the eighteenth century, our ancestor came down from that mountain valley to seek fame and fortune in the rich plains below. Those were the days of the decline of the Moghal Empire. Raj Kaul was the name of that ancestor of ours, and he had gained eminence as a Sanskrit and Persian scholar. He attracted the notice of the Emperor and, probably at his instance, the family migrated to Delhi, the imperial capital, about the year 1716. A jagir with a house situated on the banks of a canal had been granted to Raj Kaul, and, from the fact of this residence, "Nehru" (from nahar, a canal) came to be attached to his name. Kaul had been the family name; in later years, this dropped out and we became simply Nehrus.''</ref>。

